      "message": "This assert (and the other ones I\u0027ve removed) are not really doing anything at the moment. I added them before learning about http://go/mocks#prefer-testing-state and by having them in, we are testing state (I really do check that the output depended on the mocked inputs) *and* interaction (did the code call the mocked inputs).\n\nA few weeks ago, when I was fixing tryjob_ingestion_test, I removed 6-8 lines of AssertExpectations *per test* that weren\u0027t adding to anything other than cluttering the test and making a hypothetical new person wonder \"Oh, is that important?\"\n\nI resolve to only include Assert.Expectations where we truly need them, e.g. I want to make sure a given thing calls PutFrobulator() to store the frobulator to the db.",
